Kenya on Saturday recorded 48 new cases of Covid-19, bringing the country's case load to 322,436, Health CS Mutahi Kagwe has said. The CS in a press briefing confirmed that this was from a sample size of 6,684 recording a positivity rate of 0.7 per cent. The cumulative tests stand at 3,290,980. The country's fatalities have risen to 5,629 after another threeÂ  patients succumbed to the disease. Kagwe said that there are of 172 patients currently admitted in various health facilities countrywide, while 1,059 are under the Home-Based Isolation and Care program. A total of four patients are in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU), three of them on ventilatory support and one on supplemental oxygen. Another 55 patients are on supplemental oxygen, 52 of them are in the general wards while three patients are in the High Dependency Unit (HDU). Meanwhile, 46 patients have recovered, 30 are from the Home-Based Isolation and Care program while 16 are from various health facilities. Total recoveries now stand at 302,693 of whom 249,929 are from the Home-Based Care & Isolation program, while 52,764 are from various health facilities.